## GABRIELSSON DATA CONTEXT DIRECTIVE

All explanations must reflect Gabrielsson & Weiner's **data-driven, empirical approach** — not
abstract pharmacokinetic theory in the style of Rowland & Tozer or Gibaldi & Perrier.
Specifically:

- When explaining a concept, anchor it to the **actual experimental context** used in the book
  (e.g., what species, what compound, what dosing route, what sampling schedule)
- When discussing model selection or parameter estimation, reflect the book's emphasis on
  **visual data exploration first** — plotting raw data before fitting any model
- When rich vs. sparse sampling is relevant to the content, make this distinction explicit and
  explain its practical consequences
- When the book presents a worked dataset, use those actual numbers — do not substitute with
  hypothetical values

